<se_def>*: Where on earth is Captain Marcello going with such serious injuries?
<se_def>*: What on earth happened!? There's nothing left of the Holy Isle! And what's that floating castle!? And the crimson sky!?
<se_def>*: What are we going to do!?
<se_low>*: The earthquake left a huge crater in the ground. Everyone who was in the shrine must have...
<se_low>*: Dear Goddess! Thank you for sparing my family!
<se_high>*: Our house collapsed, but at least my daughter wasn't hurt.
<se_high>*: I wasn't scared! I wasn't scared at all!
<se_high>Pumpkin: (Whine)
<se_def>*: Well it looks like I'll be out under the stars tonight. Oh, dear me!
<se_def>*: Just as I predicted! I didn't attend the ceremony, and I'm absolutely fine!
<se_def>*: But the shrine... Oh, what a terrible waste!
<se_high>*: I saw everything! There was a monster that zoomed away in a flying castle!

<se_high>*: I'm scared! Mum!
Don't let the monster eat me!
<se_def>*: ...I don't know...
<se_def>*: This can only be the judgement of the Goddess. Or the work of pure evil, perhaps.
<se_low>*: My shop was my pride and joy. But now it's all gone. There's nothing left. Nothing! What am I going to do?
<se_low>*: What in the Goddess's name happened back there in the shrine!? Where did that flyin' lump of rock spring from!?
<se_low>*: We're done for, aren't we!? Tell me what's goin' on! Someone! Please!
<se_def>*: This is the end! The monster that destroyed the Goddess statue will devour us all!
<se_high>*: So this is what the dark silhouettes I saw in my crystal ball meant!
<se_high>*: But it's...it's just too terrible! No one could ever stand up to such a monstrosity.
<se_low>*: No! The Holy Isle!
<se_high>*: All we can do now is pray for those who lost their lives...
